column5: Not much time tonight to write a novel, but here is a quick rundown of yesterday's outing...  Conditions for most of the day - glass calm and sunny. Yech. Led to Al's spaghetti ski. She was 42.5", and probably 7 pounds. Rounding up. LOL! She was a hurtin' unit, but at least she was trying to eat something!  #102   Guess what happened at the end up the day when just a LITTLE bit of chop came to the water? The meatballs. They are definitely starting to pack on some pounds...  #103   #104   Thanks Al for not leaving when you wanted to... that last hour saved the day for me!
That is one sickly looking fish.
That first fish needs a big mac or two!  The last two sure are getting chubby!  You're my hero
that first ski needs a chicken carcass LOL other 2 are nice!!
I'm beginning to dread opening your posts. Serious esox envy here.  That first fish is either sick or dying of old age.
Looks like a good day. Some of the fall ski's are getting pretty fat. Your 50 incher has got to be comming soon.
Man, that poor first musky, he needs some food and love  The other ones are nice and healthy, way to go Peter  Joey
Poor little guy.... I don't think he stands a chance making it through the winter..... Did you share your lunch with him?  The other two are gorgeous
I won't be able to sleep tonight after seeing that first fish...nasty. The other two look ready for winter already, packing on some good pounds. Another great report!
what the hell is wrong with that first one?
damn that first one is uggglyy those other 2 are gorgeous tho congrats i dont know how you do it!
It's a leaf fan......hasn't had anything to feed on since '67  Couple good looking sens fans though...
Is the first one anorexic or what Some nice couple of "meatballs" as you say Pete  Question:  Ever thought of tagging the muskys you catch since you've caught so many? Leechman
I would gladly participate in a tagging program... I intend to join Muskies Canada in the near future, maybe I could get steered in the right direction there.
looks like that ski had gastric bypass surgery....gross
WOW! I bet that Musky just recently lost some jewelry( a lure stuck in his mouth).......Hopefully he/she's ok. It looks like a survivor.  Some nice musky and I know that spot anywhere!!Great spot!
